brief_summary.textblock:
This study will evaluate the safety and efficacy of 3 doses of AGN-199201 once and twice
      daily compared to vehicle for the treatment of moderate to severe facial erythema associated
      with rosacea.

clinical_study.brief_title: AGN-199201 for the Treatment of Erythema With Rosacea

The sponsor cannot require changes to the communication and cannot extend the embargo.

outcome.description: Percentage of participants with at least a 2-grade decrease from Baseline (Improvement) in the CEA score and at least a 2-grade decrease from Baseline (Improvement) in the SSA score were assessed on Day 28 hours 2 to 12. The investigator evaluated the severity of the participant's erythema (redness of the skin) as measured by the CEA using a 5-point scale where 0=clear skin with no signs of erythema; 1=almost clear of erythema, slight redness; 2=mild erythema, definite redness; 3=moderate erythema, marked redness and 4=severe erythema, fiery redness. The participant assessed the severity of their erythema as measured by the SSA using a 5-point scale where 0=clear of unwanted redness; 1=nearly clear of unwanted redness; 2=somewhat more redness than I prefer; 3=more redness than I prefer and 4=completely unacceptable redness.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Redness of the skin caused by rosacea

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  ≥3 inflammatory lesions

          -  Laser light-source or other energy based therapy in the last 6 months

          -  Any prescription or over the counter product for the treatment of acne or rosacea in
             the last 14 days
